programme.title: Duran Duran at the BBC
programme.desc: A celebration of the finest performances and appearances by the New Romantic sensations on the BBC. They came out of Birmingham in the early 80s, took over the world, and helped define the look and sound of an entire decade. Then, through constant reinvention, they kept themselves relevant even to this day. Although pioneers of the pop video age, this collection of hits and rarities - from Planet Earth to Ordinary World and beyond - captures the impact and excitement of their music on a huge selection of BBC shows, from the Old Grey Whistle Test to Wogan and, of course, Top of the Pops.

programme.title: Radio 2 in Concert
programme.desc: Highlights of the 2021 BBC Radio Theatre performance for Radio 2 In Concert from Duran Duran, the "wild boys" who formed in Birmingham in 1978 and are still going strong today. Their set includes the classics Hungry Like the Wolf, Notorious, Ordinary World, Planet Earth and Save a Prayer, plus songs from their latest album, Future Past.
